  <chapter remap="h1">
    <title>Installation</title>
     <para>After the installation procedures for regular users (this means that you have to have installed and running Erlide!), developing Erlide itself requires an additional step:</para>
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para> The Eclipse command line has to be tweaked a little bit, because some functionality is only available in this case. The arguments to add to the command line (or to the eclipse.ini file) are -vmargs -Derlide.devel=true.</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem/>
      <listitem>
        <para> Done!</para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
    <title>Note</title>
    <para>For developing Erlide, you can only use R12 at this time.</para>
  </chapter>
  <!--File: c:\programs\erlide.sf\org.erlide.help\html2\.\installationGuide.html-->
  <chapter remap="h1">
    <title>Installation guide</title>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para> Install Erlang R12 or later, if it isn&apos;t already present on your system. On Windows systems, use a path with no spaces in it.</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem/>
      <listitem>
        <para> Install Eclipse. The recommended Eclipse version is the latest 3.3 service pack.</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem/>
      <listitem>
        <para> If your network uses a proxy, fill in the appropriate data in Window-&gt;Preferences-&gt;Install/Update-&gt;Proxy settings.</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem/>
      <listitem>
        <para> Download Erlide by going to Window-&gt;Software Updates-&gt;Find and Install...-&gt;Search for new features to install. In the dialog, choose New remote site and enter Erlide as name and <ulink url="http://erlide.sourceforge.net/update">http://erlide.sourceforge.net/update</ulink> as URL. Follow the dialogs with the obvious choices and in the end you will be asked to restart.</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem/>
      <listitem>
        <para> Restart. Open Window-&gt;Preferences-&gt;Erlang-&gt;Runtime (ERTS) and enter the location of the Erlang installation. A new restart is needed, sorry about that (will fix later).</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem/>
      <listitem>
        <para> Done! You&apos;re ready to start exploring erlide</para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </chapter>
