  <chapter remap="h1">
    <title>Plugin description</title>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>
           <emphasis role="bold">erlide</emphasis>
        </para>
        <para>The feature groups together all the deliverable plugins.</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem/>
      <listitem>
        <para>
           <emphasis role="bold">erlide-basic</emphasis>
        </para>
        <para>This plugin contains the functionality necessary to configure the Erlang backend and also some utility classes.</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem/>
      <listitem>
        <para>
           <emphasis role="bold">erlide-build</emphasis>
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem/>
      <listitem>
        <para>
           <emphasis role="bold">erlide-core</emphasis>
        </para>
        <para>Here we find the classes that model the Erlang code.</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem/>
      <listitem>
        <para>
           <emphasis role="bold">erlide-debug-ui</emphasis>
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem/>
      <listitem>
        <para>
           <emphasis role="bold">erlide-devtools</emphasis>
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem/>
      <listitem>
        <para>
           <emphasis role="bold">erlide-docs</emphasis>
        </para>
        <para>Here we have no code, but administration-related files. Most notable is the source to the home page of the project in the site directory.</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem/>
      <listitem>
        <para>
           <emphasis role="bold">erlide-erlc</emphasis>
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem/>
      <listitem>
        <para>
           <emphasis role="bold">erlide-help</emphasis>
        </para>
        <para>The help files reside here. The documentation is written in Docbook format and from it we generate different formats: Eclipse help, online HTML documentation, printable PDF.</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem/>
      <listitem>
        <para>
           <emphasis role="bold">erlide-jinterface</emphasis>
        </para>
        <para>This is a wrapper around jinterface plus some minor additions.</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem/>
      <listitem>
        <para>
           <emphasis role="bold">erlide-launching</emphasis>
        </para>
        <para>This plugin manages Erlang backends.</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem/>
      <listitem>
        <para>
           <emphasis role="bold">erlide-sdk</emphasis>
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem/>
      <listitem>
        <para>
           <emphasis role="bold">erlide-testing</emphasis>
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem/>
      <listitem>
        <para>
           <emphasis role="bold">erlide-ui</emphasis>
        </para>
        <para>Here we find all UI related functionality.</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem/>
      <listitem>
        <para>
           <emphasis role="bold">erlide-update</emphasis>
        </para>
        <para>An update site is needed to distribute Erlide.</para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
