  <chapter remap="h1">
    <title>Importing an Erlang Project</title>
    <para>Import a project:</para>
    <orderedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para> Click <emphasis role="bold">File &gt; Import &gt; Erlang &gt; Import erlang project into workspace</emphasis> or <emphasis role="bold">Right click</emphasis> in <emphasis role="bold">Erlang Navigator &gt; Import...</emphasis></para>
        <para>
          <inlinemediaobject>
            <imageobject>
              <imagedata fileref="./tasks/../images/import_wizard01.png" format="PNG"/>
            </imageobject>
          </inlinemediaobject>
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para> In the Erlang Project Import Wizard, <emphasis role="bold">Browse...</emphasis> for <emphasis role="bold">Erlang project</emphasis></para>
        <para>
          <inlinemediaobject>
            <imageobject>
              <imagedata fileref="./tasks/../images/import_wizard02.png" format="PNG"/>
            </imageobject>
          </inlinemediaobject>
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para> In the source field select project.</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para> In Options you can choose to link to all folders and all files or to Copy selected files and selected folders to workspace.</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para> To import your project, click <emphasis role="bold">Finish</emphasis>.</para>
      </listitem>
    </orderedlist>
  </chapter>
  <!--File: c:\programs\erlide.sf\org.erlide.help\html2\.\tasks\erlide_new_proj.html-->
  <chapter remap="h1">
    <title>Creating a project</title>
    <para>To create a project:</para>
    <orderedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para> Click <emphasis role="bold">File &gt; New &gt; Other... &gt; Erlang Project</emphasis> or <emphasis role="bold">Right click</emphasis> in <emphasis role="bold">Erlang Navigator &gt; New Erlang Project.</emphasis></para>
        <para>
